Transfer expert, Alex Crook has provided the latest on Manchester United’s pursuit of Ajax defender Lisandro Martinez. Arsenal are also keen on signing the 24-year-old Argentine. The Red Devils recently launched an offer for him but are currently in limbo in talks over the deal. “Man United have made a €50m bid for Martínez, they’ve not been told if it’s been accepted or not. “I think he has his sights set on #MUFC. They’re his preferred destination [over Arsenal],” Crook told talkSPORT. 